  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Solving a quadratic equation after rearranging</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>
Solve the quadratic equation:
\[
{@lhs@} = {@rhs@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Write the solutions for \(x\).
</p>

<p>
\(x =\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]  \(\;or\;\) \(x =\) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]
</p>
<p>[[feedback:prt1]]  \(\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;  \) [[feedback:prt2]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
The equation given is:
</p>

<p>
\[
{@lhs@} = {@rhs@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Subtract {@rhs@} from both sides so that the equation equals zero.
</p>

<p>
\[
{@lhs@} - {@rhs@} = 0
\]
</p>

<p>
This simplifies to:
</p>

<p>
\[
{@standard@} = 0
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Factorise the quadratic expression.
</p>

<p>
\[
{@standard@}
\]
</p>

<p>
\[
= (x - {@r1@})(x - {@r2@})
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Apply the zero product rule.
</p>

<p>
If the product of two expressions is zero, then at least one of the expressions must be zero.
</p>

<p>
\[
x - {@r1@} = 0 \quad \text{or} \quad x - {@r2@} = 0
\]
</p>

<p>
Step 4: Solve each equation.
</p>

<p>
\[
x = {@r1@}
\]
</p>

<p>
or
</p>

<p>
\[
x = {@r2@}
\]
</p>

<p>
Therefore, the solutions of the quadratic equation are:
</p>

<p>
\[
x = {@r1@},\;\;or\;\; x = {@r2@}
\]
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
